briefdescription.para: Set to a previous BestRegionSummary value before connecting.

detaileddescription.para: This is a value used when the client connects to the "Best Region". If this is null or empty, all regions gets pinged. Providing a previous summary on connect, speeds up best region selection and makes the previously selected region "sticky".

Unity clients should store the BestRegionSummary in the PlayerPrefs. You can store the new result by implementing IConnectionCallbacks.OnConnectedToMaster. If LoadBalancingClient.SummaryToCache is not null, store this string. To avoid storing the value multiple times, you could set SummaryToCache to null.
